<div class="thumbinner" style="width:202px;"><a href="/wiki/File:Erving_Goffman.jpg" class="image" title="Erving Goffman"><img alt="" src="http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/en/thumb/d/de/Erving_Goffman.jpg/200px-Erving_Goffman.jpg" width="200" height="256" border="0" class="thumbimage" /></a>
<div class="thumbcaption">
<div class="magnify"><a href="/wiki/File:Erving_Goffman.jpg" class="internal" title="Enlarge"><img src="/skins-1.5/common/images/magnify-clip.png" width="15" height="11" alt="" /></a></div>
<b>Erving Goffman</b></div>
</div>
</div>
<p><b>Erving Goffman</b> (<span class="mw-formatted-date" title="1922-06-11"><span class="mw-formatted-date" title="06-11"><a href="/wiki/June_11" title="June 11">June 11</a></span>, <a href="/wiki/1922" title="1922">1922</a></span> – <span class="mw-formatted-date" title="1982-11-19"><span class="mw-formatted-date" title="11-19"><a href="/wiki/November_19" title="November 19">November 19</a></span>, <a href="/wiki/1982" title="1982">1982</a></span>), was an <a href="/wiki/United_States" title="United States">American</a>-based <a href="/wiki/Canada" title="Canada">Canadian</a> <a href="/wiki/Sociology" title="Sociology">sociologist</a> and <a href="/wiki/Writer" title="Writer">writer</a>. The <a href="/wiki/List_of_American_Sociological_Association_presidents" title="List of American Sociological Association presidents">73rd president</a> of <a href="/wiki/American_Sociological_Association" title="American Sociological Association">American Sociological Association</a>, Goffman's greatest contribution to <a href="/wiki/Social_theory" title="Social theory">social theory</a> is his study of <a href="/wiki/Symbolic_interaction" title="Symbolic interaction" class="mw-redirect">symbolic interaction</a> in the form of <a href="/wiki/Dramaturgical_perspective" title="Dramaturgical perspective" class="mw-redirect">dramaturgical perspective</a> that began with his 1956 book <i><a href="/wiki/The_Presentation_of_Self_in_Everyday_Life" title="The Presentation of Self in Everyday Life">The Presentation of Self in Everyday Life</a></i> and was developed throughout his life expanding to the topics of <a href="/wiki/Deference_and_demeanor" title="Deference and demeanor" class="mw-redirect">deference and demeanor</a>.</p>
